-- Ecuador’s Correa Plans Chavez Visit Ahead of Cuba Cancer Surgery
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2012-12-10T14:40:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-10/ecuador-s-correa-plans-chavez-visit-ahead-of-cuba-cancer-surgery.html
Ecuadorean President Rafael Correa
will visit  Venezuela ’s leader Hugo Chavez in Cuba today before
Chavez undergoes an operation for cancer, Foreign Minister
Ricardo Patino said.  “Friends accompany each other in moments of adversity,”
Patino said today in a statement on his Twitter account.  Chavez arrived today in Cuba, where he’ll undergo a fourth
operation in 18 months to treat an unspecified form of cancer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
 ngill4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Goodman at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 